02/03/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The government's Foreign Affairs and Defence Council on Tuesday (1 March) endorsed the national defence policy strategy and a document on national interests and objectives. 
Cabinet spokesman Vangelis Antonaros said the strategy outlines major threats and risks to national security -- including terrorism, arms trafficking, trans-border crime and political instability -- and spells out countermeasures. 
(ANA - 02/03/05; MPA - 01/03/05)
